ning his sons</i>, which had caused such a stir in London during his lifeti=
me. The museum won the work for $852,500.<br/><br/>The Christie=E2=80=99s l=
ot actually contained three different works of art: the painting, an engrav=
ing of the image, and a sketch for the work. Not long after, the Clark acqu=
ired a portfolio of a hundred drawings by Lethi=C3=A8re that had been part =
of the artist=E2=80=99s estate. Suddenly, with so many
works by Lethi=C3=A8re, the Clark was a leading institutional authority on =
the artist. Meslay and Bell decided to mount, as Bell put it, =E2=80=9Ca mo=
